physical_appearance: This is a photograph of the Shwedagon Pagoda in Rangoon, Burma. The photograph features the top of the Stupa in the background. On the right of the photograph, there are several roofed pagodas amongst tall trees. The pagodas look slightly worn down. There is a small clearing on the bottom-right of the photograph, with a small man-made structure. The title is written at the bottom, below the photograph.
title_text: Photograph album of views and portraits in the Punjab, Cashmere, Ceylon, Burma, Penang, Singapore, and Java Shwedagon Pagoda, Rangoon
